alleviate /əˈliːvɪˌeɪt/

(alleviating,alleviated,alleviates) 

1. V-T If you alleviate pain, suffering, or an unpleasant condition, you make it less intense or severe. 减轻 (不适) [正式] 

例： Nowadays, a great deal can be done to alleviate back pain. 如今，很多方法可以被用来减轻背部疼痛。 

2. alleviation N-UNCOUNT 减轻 [usu N 'of' n] 

例： Their energies were focused on the alleviation of the refugees' misery. 他们把精力集中在了对难民苦难的减轻上。

